properties.areaDesc: Indian Wells Valley; Kern County Desert; Fort Tejon; Tehachapi Area
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 16 at 2:32AM PST until February 17 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Westerly winds 15 to 30 mph with gusts up to 55 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Tehachapi Area, Fort Tejon, Indian Wells Valley and
Kern County Desert.

* WHEN...From noon today to 10 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
Blowing dust may reduce visibilities in some locations.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways affected include, but are not
limited to Highway 14, Highway 58 through and below Tehachapi
Pass, including the town of Mojave, and Highway 178 through and
below Walker Pass.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 10 AM PST MONDAY
